1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,500
The world is still — soft light, cool air, the hush before the day begins.

2
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:07,500
Wan doesn’t cry. Doesn’t reach. Just watches — as if releasing something long held.

3
00:00:07,500 --> 00:00:11,000
One breath. One letting go.

4
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:16,000
It climbs — small, bright, untethered — into the vast, quiet blue.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:20,000
And just like that — some things rise not to return, but to remind us how light we can be.

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:26,000
It began with a breath — light, unburdened, and entirely its own.

7
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:31,000
Gravity loosened its grip — not all at once, but gently, like a sigh.

8
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:38,000
It passed over borders no map draws — between what was known and what was possible.

9
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:46,000
Time bent around it — hours folded into minutes, distance into feeling.

10
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Even as the world darkened, it held its light — not defiantly, but tenderly.

11
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:57,000
It didn’t vanish — it remembered how to belong to something larger.

12
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:01,000
And there — not gone, but changed — it found its name among the ancient ones.

